Project Requirement: AI-Powered Chatbot with RAG Pipeline
1. Objective
Develop an AI-driven chatbot application that:
•	Uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) for accurate, context-aware responses.
•	Supports multi-modal input (text, documents, images, audio, video).
•	Provides analytics, insights, and confidence scores.
•	Implements enterprise-grade guardrails for security and compliance.
•	Enables data connectivity to multiple sources and file types.

2. Core Features
2.1 Document & Data Handling
•	Upload and process:
o	Text documents (PDF, Word)
o	Spreadsheets (CSV, Excel)
o	Images (extract text, analyze content)
o	Audio/Video files (summarize calls, meetings)
•	Extract structured and unstructured data.
•	Generate summaries, insights, and analytics from uploaded content.

2.2 RAG Pipeline
•	Vector Database Integration (e.g., Pinecone, Weaviate, FAISS).
•	Chunking & Embedding:
o	Split documents into chunks.
o	Generate embeddings using LLM-compatible models.
•	Retriever + Generator:
o	Retrieve relevant context.
o	Generate answers with confidence score.
•	Support multi-turn conversations with context retention.
2.3 Data Source Connectivity
•	Connect to:
o	SharePoint
o	Confluence
o	Azure Blob Storage
o	AWS S3 Bucket
o	REST APIs
•	Enable file upload and real-time sync.
2.4 Multi-Modal Analysis
•	Images: OCR, object detection, insights.
•	Audio/Video: Speech-to-text, summarization, key points extraction.
2.5 Guardrails & Compliance
•	Role-based access control.
•	Data encryption (in transit & at rest).
•	PII detection and masking.
•	Configurable content moderation and policy enforcement.

2.6 User Experience
•	Chat Interface:
o	Save conversations.
o	Create personas for different roles (e.g., Analyst, Developer).
•	Dashboard:
o	View insights, analytics, and confidence scores.
•	Export Options:
o	Download summaries and reports.

